o]]'' (2003).<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-roy-would-have-loved-the-bhangra-version-1012304|title=\u2018Roy would have loved the bhangra version\u2019|last=Upadhyay|first=Karishma|date=February 10, 2006|work=[[Daily News and Analysis]]|access-date=September 15, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{MetroLyrics song|roy-orbison|oh-pretty-woman}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Roy Orbison}}\n{{Van Halen}}\n\n[[Category:1964 songs]]\n[[Category:1964 singles]]\n[[Category:1976 singles]]\n[[Category:1982 singles]]\n[[Category:Roy Orbison songs]]\n[[Category:Van Halen songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Roy Orbison]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Bill Dees]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Fred Foster]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot 100 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Mainstream Rock number-one singles]]\n[[Category:UK Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:RPM Top Singles number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Germany]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Norway]]\n[[Category:Irish Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Grammy Hall of Fame Award recipients]]\n[[Category:Grammy Award for Best Male Pop Vocal Performance]]\n[[Category:United States National Recording Registry recordings]]\n[[Category:Monument Records singles]]\n[[Category:Warner Records singles]]\n[[Category:Songs about beauty]]\n", "name_user": "Bday1802", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Fixed grammar)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oh,_Pretty_Woman"}
{"title_page": "Red Punch", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name         = Red Punch\n| type         = ep\n| artist       = [[Rocket Punch]]\n| cover        = Rocket Punch - Red Punch.png\n| alt          =\n| caption      = \n| released     = {{Start date|2020|02|10}}\n| recorded     = 2019\n| studio       =\n| genre        = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[dancepop]]|[[moombahton]]|[[ballad]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.melon.com/album/detail.htm?albumId=10386406|title=RED PUNCH|website=www.melon.com}}</ref>}}\n| length       = \n| language     = Korean\n| label        = [[Woollim Entertainment|Woollim]]\n| producer     =\n| prev_title   = [[Pink Punch]]\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = Red Punch\n | type        = EP\n | single1     = Bouncy\n | single1date = February 10, 2020\n}}\n{{External music video|type=single album|{{YouTube|QqggrSpICM0|\"Bouncy\"}}}}\n}}\n\n'''''Red Punch''''' is the second [[extended play]] by South Korean girl group [[Rocket Punch]]. The album was released digitally and physically on February 10, 2020 by [[Woollim Entertainment]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=112&aid=0003266082|title=\ub85c\ucf13\ud380\uce58, \ub450 \ubc88\uc9f8 \ubbf8\ub2c8\uc568\ubc94 '\ub808\ub4dc \ud380\uce58(RED PUNCH)' \uc624\ub298(10\uc77c) \ubc1c\ub9e4|website=entertain.naver.com}}</ref> The EP contains seven tracks with the lead single \"Bouncy\".\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n|headline = ''Red Punch'' track listing\n| extra_column = Arrangement\n| total_length = 21:11\n\n| title1 = Red Punch\n| lyrics1 =\n| music1 = Code 9\n| extra1 = Code 9\n| length1 = 1:07\n\n| title2 = Bouncy\n| note2 = \n| lyrics2 = Code 9, Puravida\n| music2 = Code 9, Puravida\n| extra2 = Code 9\n| length2 = 3:28\n\n| title3 = So Solo\n| lyrics3 = Misung\n| music3 = Space One, Anna Timgren\n| extra3 = Space One\n| length3 = 3:05\n\n| title4 = Fireworks\n| lyrics4 = Llano (Stupid Squad)\n| mu